.SH ARCHITECTURES
.IP \(bu 2
ARM64 \- mostly used in phones, efficient performance
.IP \(bu 2
x86 \- older 32-bit PCs
.IP \(bu 2
x86_64 \- modern standard for PCs (Windows/Linux), best performance for desktop and gaming

.SH ASSEMBLY SYNTAX
There are two main syntaxes:
.IP \(bu 2
AT&T (GNU/Linux default)
.IP \(bu 2
Intel syntax (cleaner, commonly used in documentation)

.SH COMPILATION FLOW
High Level (C)
.br
↓
Assembly (Intel / AT&T)
.br
↓
Assembler (NASM / GAS)
.br
↓
Machine Code (0/1)
.br
↓
CPU (x86_64 / ARM64)

